He said he stands up because he feels lucky who can live openly without negative consequences and wants to give others 'hope'.
The three times the world champion said that he fell in love with a man - filmmaker Dustin Lance Black from the United States, whom he met in 2013 - « surprised me».
Daley married the Oscar winner, who is 20 years older than him, last year, but he said the age difference had never been a problem.
“When you’re so young” – he attended his first OL when he was 14 years old, and his father died of cancer three years later – he said it was hard to find someone the same age who had experienced similar ups and downs.
The couple became parents in June, to a son named Robert Ray Black-Daley, and Daley said his whole perspective had been changed.
"If you had asked me last year, everything was about me just having to win a gold medal," he said.
"You know, there are bigger things than the Olympic gold medal.
My Olympic gold medal is Robbie.
The son has the same name as his father Robert, who died in 2011 at the age of 40 after having been diagnosed with brain cancer.
Daley said that his father did not accept that he would die, and one of the last things he asked was if they had obtained tickets to London in 2012 – since he wanted to sit in the first row.
"I couldn't tell him he wouldn't live long enough to sit on the first row," he said.
"I held his hands when he stopped breathing, and it was not until he actually stopped breathing and was dead that I finally realized that he was not invincible," he said.
The following year, Daley competed in the 2012 Olympics and won bronze.
"I only knew that was what I had dreamed about all my life – to jump in front of a home audience under the Olympics, the best feeling ever," he said.
It also inspired his first song selection - Proud of Heather Small - which meant a lot to him in the drive-up before the Olympics and which still gives him goose bumps.
