When he spoke at the UN National Assembly, Foreign Minister Walid al-Moualem said that the situation in the country is improving.
‘Today, the ground situation is more stable and secure thanks to the progress to combat terrorism’ he says.
The state continues to rebuild the areas destroyed by terrorists to restore normality.
All conditions are now in place for voluntary return of refugees to the country they had to leave because of terrorism and the unilateral economic measures that affected their everyday lives and their livelihoods.
The UN estimates that more than 5.5 million acids have fled the country since the war began in 2011.
In addition, six million people still live in the country need humanitarian aid.
Al-Moualem said that the Syrian regime will accept aid to rebuild the devastated land.
But he stressed that there would not be accepted conditional assistance or assistance from countries that supported the rebellion.
